  - key: speaker.old_villager
    english: Old Villager
    indonesian: Warga Tua
  - key: subtitle.forest_warning
    english: Do not enter the forest after sundown.
    indonesian: Jangan masuk hutan setelah matahari turun.
  - key: subtitle.ancient_script_seen
    english: These symbols... I saw them near the forest.
    indonesian: Simbol ini... pernah kulihat di dekat hutan.
  - key: subtitle.player_first_see_banaspati
    english: What is that fire...?
    indonesian: Api apa itu...?
  - key: subtitle.player_first_see_banaspati_2
    english: That thing is alive.
    indonesian: Benda itu hidup.
  - key: subtitle.player_first_see_banaspati_3
    english: No... that is not normal.
    indonesian: Tidak... itu tidak normal.
  - key: subtitle.player_chased
    english: It saw me. I have to run.
    indonesian: Dia melihatku. Aku harus lari.
  - key: subtitle.player_chased_2
    english: Damn it, it is coming.
    indonesian: Sial, dia mendekat.
  - key: subtitle.player_chased_3
    english: Fuck, run. Run!
    indonesian: Anjing, lari. Lari!
  - key: subtitle.player_chased_4
    english: Do not look back. Just run.
    indonesian: Jangan lihat belakang. Lari saja.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit
    english: The heat is burning through me.
    indonesian: Panasnya membakar tubuhku.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_2
    english: Damn it, that heat hurts.
    indonesian: Sial, panasnya sakit.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_3
    english: Fuck, my skin is burning.
    indonesian: Anjing, kulitku terbakar.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_before_seeing_banaspati
    english: Something is burning my body...
    indonesian: Ada sesuatu yang membakar tubuhku...
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_before_seeing_banaspati_2
    english: What the hell is burning me...?
    indonesian: Apa yang membakarku...?
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_before_seeing_banaspati_3
    english: The air is burning my skin.
    indonesian: Udaranya membakar kulitku.
  - key: subtitle.player_burning_attack_hit
    english: This fire is pulling me in.
    indonesian: Api ini menarikku masuk.
  - key: subtitle.player_burning_attack_hit_2
    english: Fuck, it is dragging me.
    indonesian: Anjing, dia menyeretku.
  - key: subtitle.player_burning_attack_hit_3
    english: I cannot break free.
    indonesian: Aku tidak bisa lepas.
  - key: subtitle.player_low_stamina_chased
    english: I cannot keep running like this.
    indonesian: Aku tidak bisa terus berlari seperti ini.
  - key: subtitle.player_low_stamina_chased_2
    english: My legs are giving up.
    indonesian: Kakiku mulai menyerah.
  - key: subtitle.player_low_stamina_chased_3
    english: Damn it, I need air.
    indonesian: Sial, aku butuh napas.
  - key: subtitle.player_death_burn
    english: My body... is burning.
    indonesian: Tubuhku... terbakar.
  - key: subtitle.player_death_burning_attack
    english: It is dragging me into the fire.
    indonesian: Dia menyeretku ke dalam api.
  - key: subtitle.player_death_chase
    english: The fire... is lifting me.
    indonesian: Api itu... mengangkatku.
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_short
    english: Aaaa....
    indonesian: Aaaa....
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_final_large
    english: AAAAA......
    indonesian: AAAAA......
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_cutoff
    english: A....
    indonesian: A....
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_air_burn
    english: AAAAAaaaaaa...........
    indonesian: AAAAAaaaaaa...........
  - key: villager_01.name
    english: "Pak Wiryo"
    indonesian: "Pak Wiryo"
  - key: villager_01.occupation
    english: "Farmer"
    indonesian: "Petani"
  - key: villager_01.description
    english: "An experienced farmer who watches changes around the forest."
    indonesian: "Petani berpengalaman yang memperhatikan perubahan di sekitar hutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.1
    english: "Is that path the only way into the forest?"
    indonesian: "Apa jalan itu satu-satunya jalan masuk ke hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.2
    english: "It is. Finish your business before the sun goes down."
    indonesian: "Benar. Selesaikan urusanmu sebelum matahari turun."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.3
    english: "Why does everyone keep saying that?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa semua orang terus mengatakan itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.4
    english: "The birds leave before the fire comes. People should learn from them."
    indonesian: "Burung-burung pergi sebelum api datang. Manusia seharusnya belajar dari mereka."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.repeat.1
    english: "The birds go silent first?"
    indonesian: "Burung-burung akan diam lebih dahulu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.repeat.2
    english: "Yes. Turn back when the forest stops making sound."
    indonesian: "Ya. Berbaliklah saat hutan berhenti bersuara."
  - key: villager_02.name
    english: "Bu Sari"
    indonesian: "Bu Sari"
  - key: villager_02.occupation
    english: "Herbalist"
    indonesian: "Peramu Obat"
  - key: villager_02.description
    english: "A herbalist who understands flowers and traditional remedies."
    indonesian: "Peramu obat yang memahami bunga dan pengobatan tradisional."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.1
    english: "Do these flowers have any use against burns?"
    indonesian: "Apa bunga-bunga ini berguna untuk luka bakar?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.2
    english: "Separately, very little. Water from seven different kinds is another matter."
    indonesian: "Jika terpisah, hampir tidak. Air dari tujuh jenis berbeda adalah hal lain."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.3
    english: "Seven kinds?"
    indonesian: "Tujuh jenis?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.4
    english: "Old people believed they could calm heat that ordinary water cannot touch."
    indonesian: "Orang tua percaya air itu dapat menenangkan panas yang tidak bisa disentuh air biasa."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.repeat.1
    english: "The flowers must all be different?"
    indonesian: "Semua bunganya harus berbeda?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.repeat.2
    english: "Seven kinds. One missing flower changes everything."
    indonesian: "Tujuh jenis. Satu bunga yang kurang mengubah semuanya."
  - key: villager_03.name
    english: "Pak Darma"
    indonesian: "Pak Darma"
  - key: villager_03.occupation
    english: "Village Head"
    indonesian: "Kepala Desa"
  - key: villager_03.description
    english: "The village head and keeper of old expedition records."
    indonesian: "Kepala desa sekaligus penjaga catatan ekspedisi lama."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.1
    english: "I heard your family keeps old records about this forest."
    indonesian: "Aku dengar keluargamu menyimpan catatan lama tentang hutan ini."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.2
    english: "Copies of them. The oldest pages came from soldiers who never returned."
    indonesian: "Salinannya. Halaman tertua berasal dari tentara yang tidak pernah kembali."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.3
    english: "May I read them?"
    indonesian: "Boleh aku membacanya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.4
    english: "Come to my house after you have spoken with the others. Then we will decide."
    indonesian: "Datanglah ke rumahku setelah kau berbicara dengan warga lain. Setelah itu kita putuskan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.1
    english: "About those old records..."
    indonesian: "Tentang catatan lama itu..."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.2
    english: "Learn why the villagers fear the forest first. The pages will make more sense."
    indonesian: "Pelajari dulu alasan warga takut pada hutan. Halamannya akan lebih mudah dipahami."
  - key: villager_04.name
    english: "Ratri"
    indonesian: "Ratri"
  - key: villager_04.occupation
    english: "Flower Gatherer"
    indonesian: "Pemetik Bunga"
  - key: villager_04.description
    english: "A young gatherer who knows where rare flowers grow."
    indonesian: "Pemetik muda yang mengetahui tempat tumbuh bunga langka."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.1
    english: "Are all these flowers from around the village?"
    indonesian: "Apa semua bunga ini berasal dari sekitar desa?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.2
    english: "Only three kinds grow safely here. The others bloom deeper among the trees."
    indonesian: "Hanya tiga jenis yang tumbuh aman di sini. Sisanya mekar lebih dalam di antara pepohonan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.3
    english: "Why not bring the others back?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa yang lain tidak dibawa pulang?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.4
    english: "Because some paths are not worth walking twice."
    indonesian: "Karena beberapa jalan tidak layak dilewati dua kali."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.repeat.1
    english: "Three kinds grow near the village?"
    indonesian: "Tiga jenis tumbuh di dekat desa?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.repeat.2
    english: "Yes. Do not expect to find the other four outside the forest."
    indonesian: "Ya. Jangan berharap menemukan empat sisanya di luar hutan."
  - key: villager_05.name
    english: "Pak Jaya"
    indonesian: "Pak Jaya"
  - key: villager_05.occupation
    english: "Incense Trader"
    indonesian: "Pedagang Kemenyan"
  - key: villager_05.description
    english: "A trader of benzoin resin, incense, and ritual goods."
    indonesian: "Pedagang getah benzoin, kemenyan, dan perlengkapan ritual."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.1
    english: "Is this incense made from trees around here?"
    indonesian: "Apa kemenyan ini dibuat dari pohon sekitar sini?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.2
    english: "From wounded bark. Good resin comes slowly, unless the tree is touched by unusual heat."
    indonesian: "Dari kulit pohon yang dilukai. Getah bagus keluar perlahan, kecuali pohonnya tersentuh panas yang tidak biasa."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.3
    english: "Unusual heat?"
    indonesian: "Panas yang tidak biasa?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.4
    english: "You are asking for knowledge that has burned better men than us."
    indonesian: "Kau menanyakan pengetahuan yang telah membakar orang-orang yang lebih hebat dari kita."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.repeat.1
    english: "Wounded bark and heat release the resin?"
    indonesian: "Kulit terluka dan panas mengeluarkan getahnya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.repeat.2
    english: "They do. That does not mean you should try it."
    indonesian: "Benar. Bukan berarti kau harus mencobanya."
  - key: villager_06.name
    english: "Bu Marni"
    indonesian: "Bu Marni"
  - key: villager_06.occupation
    english: "Chicken Keeper"
    indonesian: "Peternak Ayam"
  - key: villager_06.description
    english: "The keeper of the village's black chickens and their eggs."
    indonesian: "Penjaga ayam hitam desa beserta telur-telurnya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.1
    english: "You keep the eggs separated. Is there a reason?"
    indonesian: "Telur-telur itu dipisahkan. Apa ada alasannya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.2
    english: "Every egg has its own time. Mixing them makes it easy to choose the wrong one."
    indonesian: "Setiap telur punya waktunya sendiri. Mencampurnya membuat orang mudah memilih yang salah."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.3
    english: "How can you tell them apart?"
    indonesian: "Bagaimana membedakannya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.4
    english: "Use your hands and your judgment. I will not choose for you."
    indonesian: "Gunakan tangan dan penilaianmu. Aku tidak akan memilihkan untukmu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.repeat.1
    english: "You really will not tell me which egg to take?"
    indonesian: "Kau benar-benar tidak mau memberi tahu telur mana yang harus kuambil?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.repeat.2
    english: "A choice without understanding is still the wrong choice."
    indonesian: "Pilihan tanpa pemahaman tetaplah pilihan yang salah."
  - key: villager_07.name
    english: "Ki Surya"
    indonesian: "Ki Surya"
  - key: villager_07.occupation
    english: "Village Elder"
    indonesian: "Tetua Desa"
  - key: villager_07.description
    english: "An elder who preserves the oldest oral history of Banaspati."
    indonesian: "Tetua yang menjaga sejarah lisan tertua tentang Banaspati."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.1
    english: "What do the villagers call the fire in the forest?"
    indonesian: "Apa sebutan warga untuk api di dalam hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.2
    english: "Banaspati. The foreign soldiers called it the Ashes That Remember."
    indonesian: "Banaspati. Tentara asing menyebutnya Ashes That Remember."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.3
    english: "Why ashes that remember?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa abu yang mengingat?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.4
    english: "Because it remembers every human who left it trapped in this world."
    indonesian: "Karena ia mengingat setiap manusia yang membuatnya terjebak di dunia ini."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.1
    english: "Banaspati remembers humans?"
    indonesian: "Banaspati mengingat manusia?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.2
    english: "It remembers, and its anger has had centuries to grow."
    indonesian: "Ia mengingat, dan amarahnya telah tumbuh selama berabad-abad."
  - key: villager_08.name
    english: "Wulan"
    indonesian: "Wulan"
  - key: villager_08.occupation
    english: "Water Carrier"
    indonesian: "Pembawa Air"
  - key: villager_08.description
    english: "A water carrier familiar with springs and ceremonial flower water."
    indonesian: "Pembawa air yang mengenal mata air dan air bunga upacara."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.1
    english: "Why is that flower water kept in a sealed vessel?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa air bunga itu disimpan dalam wadah tertutup?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.2
    english: "Because protection is spent when it is used. A careless person empties it before it matters."
    indonesian: "Karena perlindungannya berkurang saat digunakan. Orang ceroboh menghabiskannya sebelum dibutuhkan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.3
    english: "Can ordinary river water replace it?"
    indonesian: "Apa air sungai biasa bisa menggantikannya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.4
    english: "For thirst, yes. For an eternal flame, no."
    indonesian: "Untuk haus, bisa. Untuk api abadi, tidak."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.repeat.1
    english: "So I should not waste the flower water?"
    indonesian: "Jadi air bunganya tidak boleh disia-siakan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.repeat.2
    english: "Use it only when the fire leaves you no other choice."
    indonesian: "Gunakan hanya saat api tidak memberimu pilihan lain."
  - key: villager_09.name
    english: "Bima"
    indonesian: "Bima"
  - key: villager_09.occupation
    english: "Hunter"
    indonesian: "Pemburu"
  - key: villager_09.description
    english: "A hunter who stopped entering the forest after a close encounter."
    indonesian: "Pemburu yang berhenti memasuki hutan setelah mengalami pertemuan berbahaya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.1
    english: "You know the forest trails?"
    indonesian: "Kau tahu jalur-jalur di hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.2
    english: "I used to. Now the trails change whenever that light begins following someone."
    indonesian: "Dulu aku tahu. Sekarang jalurnya berubah setiap kali cahaya itu mulai mengikuti seseorang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.3
    english: "It follows people?"
    indonesian: "Ia mengikuti manusia?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.4
    english: "Once it marks you, a tree or wall only delays it."
    indonesian: "Begitu ia menandaimu, pohon atau dinding hanya memperlambatnya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.repeat.1
    english: "Can I hide after it sees me?"
    indonesian: "Apa aku bisa bersembunyi setelah ia melihatku?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.repeat.2
    english: "Create distance. Hiding nearby will only buy a few breaths."
    indonesian: "Jauhkan dirimu. Bersembunyi di dekatnya hanya memberimu beberapa tarikan napas."
  - key: villager_10.name
    english: "Seno"
    indonesian: "Seno"
  - key: villager_10.occupation
    english: "Woodcutter"
    indonesian: "Penebang Kayu"
  - key: villager_10.description
    english: "A woodcutter who recognizes heat-damaged trees and valuable resin."
    indonesian: "Penebang kayu yang mengenali pohon rusak karena panas dan getah berharga."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.1
    english: "Some trees have black scars. Was there a fire?"
    indonesian: "Beberapa pohon punya luka hitam. Apa pernah terjadi kebakaran?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.2
    english: "No ordinary fire. The bark burned while the leaves remained green."
    indonesian: "Bukan api biasa. Kulitnya terbakar sementara daunnya tetap hijau."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.3
    english: "Did anything remain in the wound?"
    indonesian: "Apa ada sesuatu yang tersisa di lukanya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.4
    english: "Clear resin. It hardens into incense if you survive long enough to collect it."
    indonesian: "Getah bening. Getah itu mengeras menjadi kemenyan jika kau bertahan cukup lama untuk mengambilnya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.1
    english: "The resin appears in the burned wound?"
    indonesian: "Getahnya muncul pada luka yang terbakar?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.2
    english: "Yes. Cut first, then heat. Keep your hands ready to run."
    indonesian: "Ya. Lukai dulu, lalu panaskan. Pastikan kakimu siap berlari."
  - key: villager_11.name
    english: "Laras"
    indonesian: "Laras"
  - key: villager_11.occupation
    english: "Weaver"
    indonesian: "Penenun"
  - key: villager_11.description
    english: "A weaver whose family preserved an artifact from a colonial expedition."
    indonesian: "Penenun yang keluarganya menyimpan benda dari ekspedisi masa kolonial."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.1
    english: "That insignia does not look local."
    indonesian: "Lambang itu tidak terlihat berasal dari sini."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.2
    english: "It belonged to a soldier my ancestor found half-burned near the forest edge."
    indonesian: "Itu milik tentara yang ditemukan leluhurku dalam keadaan setengah terbakar di tepi hutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.3
    english: "Did the soldier say what happened?"
    indonesian: "Apa tentara itu mengatakan apa yang terjadi?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.4
    english: "Only two words before he died: it remembers."
    indonesian: "Hanya dua kata sebelum ia mati: ia mengingat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.repeat.1
    english: "The soldier said it remembers?"
    indonesian: "Tentara itu berkata ia mengingat?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.repeat.2
    english: "Those words survived longer than the man who spoke them."
    indonesian: "Kata-kata itu bertahan lebih lama daripada orang yang mengucapkannya."
  - key: villager_12.name
    english: "Tono"
    indonesian: "Tono"
  - key: villager_12.occupation
    english: "Mechanic"
    indonesian: "Mekanik"
  - key: villager_12.description
    english: "The village mechanic responsible for keeping old vehicles running."
    indonesian: "Mekanik desa yang menjaga kendaraan tua tetap berjalan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.1
    english: "Will the vehicle be ready if I need to leave quickly?"
    indonesian: "Apa kendaraannya siap jika aku harus pergi dengan cepat?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.2
    english: "The engine is ready. The road is the problem once the rain starts."
    indonesian: "Mesinnya siap. Jalannya yang jadi masalah saat hujan mulai turun."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.3
    english: "Keep it facing the city."
    indonesian: "Pastikan arahnya menghadap kota."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.4
    english: "Already done. I do not ask why people run from that forest anymore."
    indonesian: "Sudah. Aku tidak lagi bertanya kenapa orang berlari dari hutan itu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.repeat.1
    english: "The vehicle is still ready?"
    indonesian: "Kendaraannya masih siap?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.repeat.2
    english: "Fueled and facing out. Do not make me wait after midnight."
    indonesian: "Bahan bakarnya penuh dan menghadap keluar. Jangan membuatku menunggu lewat tengah malam."
  - key: villager_13.name
    english: "Bu Ningsih"
    indonesian: "Bu Ningsih"
  - key: villager_13.occupation
    english: "Cook"
    indonesian: "Juru Masak"
  - key: villager_13.description
    english: "A cook who sells food and prepares supplies for travelers."
    indonesian: "Juru masak yang menjual makanan dan menyiapkan bekal perjalanan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.1
    english: "I need supplies that will last in the forest."
    indonesian: "Aku butuh bekal yang tahan lama di hutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.2
    english: "Take dry food and water. Do not carry more than you can run with."
    indonesian: "Bawa makanan kering dan air. Jangan membawa lebih dari yang bisa kau bawa saat berlari."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.3
    english: "Everyone assumes I will have to run."
    indonesian: "Semua orang menganggap aku harus berlari."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.4
    english: "Those who did not run are not here to advise you."
    indonesian: "Mereka yang tidak berlari sudah tidak ada untuk menasihatimu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.repeat.1
    english: "Light supplies, then?"
    indonesian: "Jadi bawa bekal ringan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.repeat.2
    english: "Enough to survive, never enough to slow your feet."
    indonesian: "Cukup untuk bertahan, jangan sampai memperlambat kakimu."
  - key: villager_14.name
    english: "Agus"
    indonesian: "Agus"
  - key: villager_14.occupation
    english: "Night Guard"
    indonesian: "Penjaga Malam"
  - key: villager_14.description
    english: "The night guard who watches the village boundary facing the forest."
    indonesian: "Penjaga malam yang mengawasi batas desa menghadap hutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.1
    english: "What do you watch for at night?"
    indonesian: "Apa yang kau awasi saat malam?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.2
    english: "A light moving against the wind. When I see it, I ring the bell once."
    indonesian: "Cahaya yang bergerak melawan angin. Saat melihatnya, aku membunyikan lonceng sekali."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.3
    english: "Why only once?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa hanya sekali?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.4
    english: "A second ring would mean it has already reached the village."
    indonesian: "Bunyi kedua berarti ia sudah mencapai desa."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.repeat.1
    english: "One bell means the light is moving?"
    indonesian: "Satu bunyi lonceng berarti cahayanya bergerak?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.repeat.2
    english: "Yes. If you hear two, do not waste time looking outside."
    indonesian: "Ya. Jika kau mendengar dua, jangan buang waktu melihat keluar."
  - key: villager_15.name
    english: "Dewi"
    indonesian: "Dewi"
  - key: villager_15.occupation
    english: "Teacher"
    indonesian: "Guru"
  - key: villager_15.description
    english: "A teacher studying the old script used in the village archives."
    indonesian: "Guru yang mempelajari aksara lama dalam arsip desa."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.1
    english: "Can you read the symbols in the old documents?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau bisa membaca simbol dalam dokumen lama?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.2
    english: "Some of them. The same shapes are carved inside the village head's house."
    indonesian: "Sebagiannya. Bentuk yang sama terukir di dalam rumah kepala desa."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.3
    english: "Is there a complete alphabet?"
    indonesian: "Apa ada alfabet lengkap?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.4
    english: "There is a comparison sheet. Once you study it, the repeated patterns become readable."
    indonesian: "Ada lembar perbandingan. Setelah kau mempelajarinya, pola yang berulang akan bisa dibaca."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.repeat.1
    english: "The comparison sheet is in the village head's house?"
    indonesian: "Lembar perbandingannya ada di rumah kepala desa?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.repeat.2
    english: "Yes. Remember the shapes before you enter the forest."
    indonesian: "Ya. Ingat bentuknya sebelum kau memasuki hutan."
  - key: villager_16.name
    english: "Raka"
    indonesian: "Raka"
  - key: villager_16.occupation
    english: "Village Youth"
    indonesian: "Pemuda Desa"
  - key: villager_16.description
    english: "A restless young villager who once followed a strange light."
    indonesian: "Pemuda desa yang pernah mengikuti cahaya aneh."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.1
    english: "You have seen the fire yourself?"
    indonesian: "Kau pernah melihat api itu sendiri?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.2
    english: "Only from far away. It moved like it was searching for someone."
    indonesian: "Hanya dari jauh. Gerakannya seperti sedang mencari seseorang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.3
    english: "And you followed it?"
    indonesian: "Dan kau mengikutinya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.4
    english: "For a minute. The heat found me before the light turned around."
    indonesian: "Selama satu menit. Panasnya menemukanku sebelum cahayanya berbalik."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.repeat.1
    english: "The heat reached you from far away?"
    indonesian: "Panasnya mencapaimu dari jauh?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.repeat.2
    english: "Farther than I expected. Walls did not make it disappear."
    indonesian: "Lebih jauh dari perkiraanku. Dinding tidak membuatnya menghilang."
  - key: villager_17.name
    english: "Mbah Karto"
    indonesian: "Mbah Karto"
  - key: villager_17.occupation
    english: "Storyteller"
    indonesian: "Pencerita"
  - key: villager_17.description
    english: "The oldest storyteller, keeper of the forbidden warrior legend."
    indonesian: "Pencerita tertua yang menjaga legenda pendekar terlarang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.1
    english: "How did Banaspati become trapped here?"
    indonesian: "Bagaimana Banaspati bisa terjebak di sini?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.2
    english: "A warrior opened a path to hell, seeking strength that was never meant for humans."
    indonesian: "Seorang pendekar membuka jalan ke neraka, mencari kekuatan yang tidak ditujukan bagi manusia."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.3
    english: "The warrior summoned it?"
    indonesian: "Pendekar itu memanggilnya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.4
    english: "Yes. Banaspati burned him to bone, but the gate closed before the creature could return."
    indonesian: "Ya. Banaspati membakarnya hingga menjadi tulang, tetapi gerbang tertutup sebelum makhluk itu bisa kembali."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.repeat.1
    english: "So the warrior's ritual trapped it?"
    indonesian: "Jadi ritual pendekar itu menjebaknya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.repeat.2
    english: "That is why its hatred belongs to every human it sees."
    indonesian: "Itulah sebabnya kebenciannya tertuju pada setiap manusia yang dilihatnya."
  - key: villager_18.name
    english: "Yuni"
    indonesian: "Yuni"
  - key: villager_18.occupation
    english: "Shopkeeper"
    indonesian: "Pemilik Toko"
  - key: villager_18.description
    english: "The general shopkeeper who sells limited expedition equipment."
    indonesian: "Pemilik toko umum yang menjual perlengkapan ekspedisi terbatas."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.1
    english: "I cannot afford all of this equipment."
    indonesian: "Uangku tidak cukup untuk membeli semua perlengkapan ini."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.2
    english: "Then choose what solves a problem you cannot solve in the forest."
    indonesian: "Kalau begitu pilih benda yang menyelesaikan masalah yang tidak bisa kau atasi di hutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.3
    english: "What would you choose?"
    indonesian: "Apa yang akan kau pilih?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.4
    english: "I sell choices, not certainty. Ask what each item was made for."
    indonesian: "Aku menjual pilihan, bukan kepastian. Tanyakan kegunaan setiap barang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.repeat.1
    english: "There is no discount for taking everything?"
    indonesian: "Tidak ada potongan harga untuk membeli semuanya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.repeat.2
    english: "No. Your limited money is part of the choice."
    indonesian: "Tidak. Uangmu yang terbatas adalah bagian dari pilihan."
  - key: villager_19.name
    english: "Pak Hasan"
    indonesian: "Pak Hasan"
  - key: villager_19.occupation
    english: "Cemetery Keeper"
    indonesian: "Penjaga Makam"
  - key: villager_19.description
    english: "A cemetery keeper familiar with old death rites and their symbols."
    indonesian: "Penjaga makam yang memahami ritual kematian lama dan perlambangannya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.1
    english: "Why would an old ritual require something that never lived?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa ritual lama membutuhkan sesuatu yang tidak pernah hidup?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.2
    english: "Not something that never lived. Something whose life ended before it began."
    indonesian: "Bukan sesuatu yang tidak pernah hidup. Sesuatu yang hidupnya berakhir sebelum dimulai."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.3
    english: "What purpose would that serve?"
    indonesian: "Apa kegunaannya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.4
    english: "The dead know the road to death. Old rituals used them as guides."
    indonesian: "Yang mati mengetahui jalan menuju kematian. Ritual lama menggunakan mereka sebagai penuntun."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.repeat.1
    english: "A life that ended before birth becomes the guide?"
    indonesian: "Kehidupan yang berakhir sebelum lahir menjadi penuntun?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.repeat.2
    english: "That is what the old rites believed. Do not confuse it with an ordinary sacrifice."
    indonesian: "Itulah kepercayaan ritual lama. Jangan samakan dengan pengorbanan biasa."
